 Finally, historical Bartonella host-switching was more frequent for closely related bats after accounting for sampling bias among bat species. This study helps to disentangle the complex ecology and evolution of Bartonella bacteria in bat species and their arthropod vectors. Our work provides insight into the important mechanisms that partition parasite communities among hosts, particularly the effect of host phylogeny and roost sharing, and could help to elucidate the evolutionary patterns of other diverse vector-borne microorganisms.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "McKee, Clifton D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Krawczyk, Aleksandra I.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "S\u00e1ndor, Attila D.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "G\u00f6rf\u00f6l, Tam\u00e1s", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "F\u00f6ldv\u00e1ri, Mih\u00e1ly", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "F\u00f6ldv\u00e1ri, G\u00e1bor", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Dekeukeleire, Daan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Haarsma, Anne-Jifke", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kosoy, Michael Y.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Webb, Colleen T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sprong, Hein", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/fd5e03324372209f1e5fc351d6f7853c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/c6541b29c99e656cc0a5864b42931bcb0b5e3c6640d097c16955e6be8bdec25c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/A8H57S4X", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/A8H57S4X", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/568ef57b8eca693e0fdb7e9fd3c597e0!/b190257-192718", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e